# attn:seeker brand rules

You are building the attn:seeker website. Follow these rules on every file you create or modify. No exceptions.

## Fonts
- Display/headlines: Obviously (geometric sans). Always lowercase.
- Body/editorial: Tiempos (warm serif). Always sentence case.
- Obviously leads, Tiempos follows. Never stack two Obviously elements without Tiempos between, except in navigation/UI.
- Personal quotes from Stanley Henry: sentence case in Tiempos (exception to lowercase rule).

## Font variants
- H1: Obviously Wide Bold, 72px desktop / 40px mobile
- H2: Obviously Wide SemiBold, 48px / 32px
- H3: Obviously Wide SemiBold, 32px / 24px
- H4: Obviously Wide Medium, 24px / 20px
- Labels/buttons/nav: Obviously Medium, 16px / 14px
- Stat numbers: Obviously Narrow Black, 64px / 40px
- Captions/metadata: Obviously Regular, 13px / 12px
- Body large: Tiempos Text Regular, 20px / 18px
- Body standard: Tiempos Text Regular, 18px / 16px
- Pull quotes: Tiempos Headline Medium, 28px / 22px

## Colours
- Red: #FF0000 (spotlight, CTAs, headlines in Obviously only)
- Bone: #FAF6E7 (default background for everything)
- Black: #000000 (text, structure)
- White: #FFFFFF (functional elements on bone: inputs, cards, modals)
- Dark red: #CC0000 (hover states only)
- Secondary text: black at 55% opacity
- NO GREY ANYWHERE. Not as text, backgrounds, or borders.
- No desaturated reds. No salmon, coral, burgundy.
- No drop shadows.

## Surfaces
- Bone = default background
- White = inputs, cards, modals, panels (things that sit ON bone)
- Black = footer, streaming mode, earned impact moments
- Red = hero blocks, CTAs, sparingly
- On dark/red surfaces, use bone (#FAF6E7) for text, not white

## Components
- Images/video: 0px radius (sharp corners, always)
- Buttons/inputs/cards: 8px radius
- Tags/pills: 20px radius (full round)
- Buttons: primary (red bg, bone text), secondary (black bg, bone text), ghost (transparent, red border, red text)
- Cards: white bg on bone, no border, no shadow, 24px padding, 8px radius. Use sparingly.
- Line borders: 1px black at 10-15% opacity. For dividing content groups, not sections.
- No drop shadows anywhere.

## Spacing (8px base grid)
- xs: 8px, sm: 16px, md: 24px, lg: 32px, xl: 48px, 2xl: 64px, 3xl: 96px, 4xl: 128px
- Containers: narrow 600px, content 800px, standard 900px, wide 1000px, full 1100px

## Three design modes
1. Editorial (articles, learn, topics): bone bg, line borders for structure, Tiempos leads, dense but readable
2. Brand (homepage, agency, about, services, contact): bone bg, generous spacing, Obviously leads, spacious
3. Streaming (shows, podcasts, episodes): dark/black bg, thumbnail-driven, Obviously for everything, Netflix/Spotify feel

## Writing rules
- NO EM DASHES. Use commas or periods.
- All headings, labels, buttons: lowercase
- Body text: normal sentence case
- Direct, confident tone
- No corporate jargon

## Technical
- Next.js 14 App Router with TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- All data currently uses mock data from src/data/mock/
- Auth: Memberstack (stubbed with useAuth hook)
- Search: Algolia (stubbed with useSearch hook)
- Backend: Xano API (stubbed with mock data)
- Always include loading states and error states
- Mobile-first responsive design
- All images use next/image with proper alt text

## File patterns
- Page components: src/app/[route]/page.tsx
- Shared components: src/components/ui/ for design system, src/components/layout/ for global
- Types: src/types/
- Mock data: src/data/mock/
- Utilities: src/lib/

## Reference docs
- Read docs/design-system.md for full brand specifications
- Read docs/cms-structure.md for CMS field definitions
- Read docs/page-map.md for page list and design modes
